name: Ring / Vercingétorix
description:
The Motorious Archimbaud ring collection.

Exclusively sold by Motorious in Northern Europe.

The Archimbaud family has been sculpting for over two generations in France, with our friend Alex's father, Jean-Marc, starting the profession in the mid-1960’s at the age of 13. During the early 1970’s he traveled across America in a V8 powered Oldsmobile with his girlfriend at the time, Martha, soaking in Janis Joplin, Pink Floyd, Ray Charles, the culture and counter-culture, and became intimately acquianted with the Native American cultures in the Dakota’s and in Northern Canada. A deep connection between man, land and beast inspired a collection of rings that he began then, and still continues today.

The Lost Wax Casting Method
Sculpting rings bespoke by appointment only, Jean-Marc works out of Paris creating his pieces by hand, painstakingly using the oldest effective technique available, CIRE PERDUE (Lost Wax Casting), a technique dating back to the time of the Pharaoh’s, a method that calls for first creating a wax sculpture, that is molded and melted away in the process (hence the name “lost wax”), giving way to a mold capable of taking molten precious metals.

All creations are J.M. Archimbaud's interpretations of the motifs and ideas of his youth, authentic creations originating from the era when the roads still ran wild, and the music wilder. Custom rings can be created upon demand, and any and all rings for sale are made exclusively for the individual. We do not stock rings in standard sizes, each piece will be created using your wishes and measurements. 

Material
Our Fondeur in Paris delivers all rings in 950 silver, unless alternatives are requested.
Any and all (optional) precious stones will be chosen and set in Copenhagen.

How to order
All rings are custom-made upon order.
Delivery time: 6-12 weeks.
Email info@motorious.dk to learn more

name: Loewen Messer pocket knife
description:
Street legal pocket knife.

The Loewen Messer knife factury in Germany is an epic knife producer within the pocket knife segment. The craftsmanship is of an extraordinary quality and the factory has produced knifes since 1840. This specific knife has been customized for Motorious. Our logo has been carved in the wooden handle.
The unlockable blade has a length of 6.9 cm with is within the 7 cm that is the legal knife length limit in Denmark. If you plan to use it outside Denmark, please check with local laws. The steel is not the flimsy steal less quality, but true old school steel that with stay sharp for a long period of time.

name: The Ride
description:
New Custom Motorcycles and Their Builders

The motorcycle is back! Similar to the fresh contemporary scene that has established itself around bicycles in the last few years, the motorcycle is currently undergoing an aesthetic rebirth. A young subculture worldwide is discovering the motorcycle as an expression of its personality and creativity.


The Ride explores motorcycle riding as it is meant to be: as a means of getting around with attitude, as an extension of one’s own body, as an expression of personal freedom, but also as a significant challenge to technical expertise, craftsmanship, physics, discipline, and driving skill.

Editors: Chris Hunter, Robert Klanten
Hardcover: 320 pages
Publisher: Gestalten (September 13, 2013)

name: Danish Tattooing
description:
Danish Tattooing” traces the visual development from 1895 up to the present day, with the Golden Age of the 1960s particularly rich on fascinating tales from a rough scene. The book is full of anecdotes and historical photographs of larger-than-life characters and tattooing hotspots: the raw Nyhavn, where sailors and drunk Swedes got their tattoos, and the even rougher Istedgade, which developed into a new tattooing hub in the 1980s. Actually, Copenhagen was the heart and soul of tattooing in Scandinavia until the mid-seventies. The book returns to the present by portraying 14 working tattoo artists, along with their distinctive artwork.

Author: Jon Nordstrøm
Paperback: 296 pages
Publisher: Gingko Press Inc. (June 3, 2013)
Language: English
Product Dimensions: 1.1 x 7.9 x 9.8 inches

name: Engel Original Thermal Jacket / Blue
description:
F. Engel is well-known for its workwear. Ever since 1927, when Carl J. Engel Sr. brought a pair of Bull Denim bib overalls back with him from the United States, the company has manufactured durable workwear for several generations of Danish craftsmen.

This thermal jacket was originally made to be worn under the worker’s normal work jacket - to keep out the cold. 
This is why the jacket has a longer back piece. 
The big pockets at front and the chest pocket were meant to be used - and is a must for workwear. 
Originally, the thermal jacket was much more loose-fitting as workers need space for movement.
In this new version of the thermal jacket we have only altered the fitting - the rest is history!

100% polyester

name: Gasoline Magazine #3
description:
Gasoline Magazine är en tidskrift skapad av ett gäng motorentusiaster som testade om det gick att göra en tidning med ett innehåll vi själva gillade, helt utan kompromisser. I januari 2006 kom det första numret av Gasoline Magazine ut och bevisligen gjorde vi något ni läsare uppskattar, då vi nu snart sju år senare är en av landets ledande motortidningar.

Gänget bakom Gasoline har under åren växt.  I dagsläget är vi över 20 personer som ser till att snappa upp och dokumentera det bästa inom det vi gillar mest, nämligen hot rods, kustoms, muskelbilar, motorcyklar och racing. Oavsett om det är ett bygge som kostat 2 000 kronor eller en miljon att slå ihop, så ska det inspirera. Det är vårt mål.

Vi har hela tiden strävat efter att hålla en hög nivå, både gällande foto, layout och papperskvalité, vilket gör Gasoline unikt.

Under 2012 fortsätter vi utvecklas och en stor nyhet är att vi från och med juni månad går över till månadsutgivning och breddar innehållet. Resten får bli en överraskning.

Vi fortsätter att göra det vi tycker är kul och själva vill läsa om och hoppas att det faller er läsare i smaken även i fortsättningen.

www.gasolinemagazine.se

name: DicE Magazine issue #49
description: "If you have gearhead tendencies and want to see the sort of one off bikes that are being put together in the basements, garages, and woodsheds around the world. . . the bikes that are fondled by the wild-eyed and sleepless. . .then here you are on the right path to two-wheeled glory, before your annoying neighbour comes roaring up like he just came off the set of 'Scorpio Rising: part 2' and tries to talk to you about how cool his new factory endorsed riding jacket is. DicE takes a more casual approach to topics taken seriously by others. It makes your interests more fun and not just some facts thrown on the page for nerds. The general approach is along the lines of the early issues of Big Brother and music fan zines. Some words set to the printed images add so much to the story. DicE is hands down the coolest underground motorcycle magazines out there"

name: Kustomposten #2
description:
Kustomposten er et trykt dansk blad indenfor subkulturen omkring rockabilly og klassiske biler og motorcykler. Du kender måske lignende udenlandske blade som Dice, Rolls & Pleats, Primer, Bachelor Pad, Smoking Shut Down, Fuel m.fl. Jeg er selv ivrig læser af de blade og synes det kunne være fedt hvis vi havde et lignende blad i Danmark.

Omdrejningspunktet for Kustomposten vil være de ting der går under betegnelsen “Kustom Kulture”. Dvs. Ombyggede biler og motorcykler af ældre dato, Hot Rod’s, Kustoms, Low riders, Choppers, Bobbers, og hvad det nu ellers hedder. Jeg tænker også at berøre kunsten indenfor kulturen typisk kaldet “low brow art” og pinstriping.

Læs blandt andet om:

De fedeste biler fra Hot Rod Reunion 2010

Den hårdkogte sandhed om The Uninvited MC

Hot Rod kulturen raser i det gamle østtyskland

Kunsten at tegne en cool custom bil

Uskyldige unge mænd besat af Johnny Cash

name: Sideburn Magazine issue #13
description: The Sideburn is a dirty bike lifestyle title that celebrates the stripped-back, bull-free, go-fast, turn-let ethos and aesthetic of dirt track racing. It also digs improbable road trips; widowmaker hillclimbs; shed-built; home-brewed racebikes; have-a-go heroes; hopeless zeroes and unearthing stories no one has ever written or read before. Sideburn attracts contributions from the finest writers, photographers and racers in motorcycles.

name: Greasy Kulture Magazine #35
description:
GKM is published six times a year and features traditionally-styled custom bikes – and yes, occasionally cars – from around the world.

Issues one to 30 were digest (A5) sized, full colour and each had around 70 pages – all nice, heavyweight paper. Issues 31 up are slightly larger (between A5 and normal magazine size) and thicker… same great content.

Bikes featured come from the USA, UK, Japan, Australia and Europe. We have also featured bikes from as far away as Java and Malaysia. Try the mag: if you hate it, send it back and we’ll refund you!

If you’re looking for issues 1, 2, 3, 4 and 9… sorry, they’re long gone. Wish we’d kept a few more of them for the pension fund.

name: Flake & Flames DVD
description:
Flake & Flames is a fantastic adventure through the Kustom Kulture movement around the globe seeking out the hottest Kustom Kulture spots in the United States (US) and Europe.

If you are new to Kustom Kulture, you will experience the overwhelming creativity that exists behind terms like Low Brow Art, Hot Rods, Customs, and Pinstriping. Those who are familiar with Kustom Kulture will drool in awe and get a privileged look into the private domain of the Kustom Kulture legends of our time.

Some of the world’s best car and motorcycle builders, tattoo artists, pinstripers, custom painters, and pin-up models share their tricks and experience. Artists dedicated to art forms that have traditionally been frowned upon by established society throughout history show you why nothing else can compare.

Producer: Jesper Bram
Executive Producer: Hell Yeah Beer // Bram Kustom Graphics
Directors: Jesper Bram & Dirk Behlau
Director of Photography: Dirk Behlau
Co-Director: Daniel Alban
Filmed by: Jesper Bram & Dirk Behlau
Edited by: Daniel Alban at Kong Gulerod Film
Language: English, 80min
Feature length documentary
The film is an independent production

name: Cyklen på Nørrebro
description:
Language: Danish only

Cyklen på Nørrebro, er en bog om Københavns vigtigste bydel, Nørrebro, kun her er der ikke mere end 150 meter mellem Cykelsmedene, kun her har alle en Cykel, måske to, kun her har jeg taget billederne til denne bog, en bog lavet med kærlighed til Cyklen, cyklisterne og bydelen.

af Jon Nordstrøm

name: Nordic Tattooing
description:
A historical book of tattooing from Jon Nordstrøm the writer of Danish Tattooing. name: Engel Original Thermal Vest / Blue
description:
F. Engel is well-known for its workwear. Ever since 1927, when Carl J. Engel Sr. brought a pair of Bull Denim bib overalls back with him from the United States, the company has manufactured durable workwear for several generations of Danish craftsmen.

This thermal vest was originally made to be worn under the worker’s normal work jacket - to keep out the cold. 
The big pockets at front and the chest pocket were meant to be used - and is a must for workwear. 
Originally, the vest was much more loose-fitting as workers need space for movement. 
In this new version of the thermal vest we have only altered the fitting - the rest is history!

100% polyester

Its all about the love for vintage custom and classic motorcycles, so start up your bobbers, choppers, stockers and cafe racers and ride to the castle. Everyone is welcome!! So please come and join us for either the whole weekend or just for the day. As well as vintage motorcycles there will be food, music, venders, a ride out, prizes, camping and lots and lots of BEER.

name: KD's
description:
KD's are The Original Biker Shades®. The Sons of Anarchy TV show chose our sunglasses because nothing screams biker like The Original KD's. KD's are the #1 Selling Biker Sunglass in the World and THE motorcycle riding glasses that bikers everywhere ask for by name.

This little black framed sunglass has been extremely popular with bikers for over 60 years because they stay on your head and keep the wind out of your eyes by fitting tightly on the temples and nosebridge. And most importantly, KD sunglasses look cool. For those searching for polarized sunglasses you will be happy to know that we offer KD's with a polarized grey lens (#2019) as well as a lot of other color lenses. And by the way, KD's aren't just sunglasses for men; women love the performance, style and variety of lens colors KD's offer.

Bikers made them famous, but everyone loves The Original KD's®.

description: Indian Larry was born in New York and was interested in mechanics from a very early age.
